rooms.Name: Walking down a road.
rooms.Description:
Walking past the rubble you can spot a top of a huge Cathedral ahead. It's
towers must be about 100 feet in the air. You wonder who lives, or resides, in
that monsterous building. There is a path ahead that turns into a well paved
road about 50 feet from you.

rooms.Name: On a road.
rooms.Description:
As you walk along the path you see the Cathedral rise up before you. It is a
dark, evil looking place. It is made of black granite, or some other smooth
type of stone. There are no other roads leading to the Cathedral, only this
one. Beyond the Cathedral you see some mountains and a ship orbiting in the
sky.

rooms.Name: On the steps on the Cathedral
rooms.Description:
Walking closer to the Cathedral you can now make out more shapes that lurk
around the walls and on the battlements. They depict small furried creatures
and gargolyes. There are large cannons and turrets built into the towers and
some of the battlements the look as if they could destroy whole ships in just
one volley. This is a very fortified position. The road continues on straight
toward the Cathedral.

rooms.Name: On the steps of the cathedral
rooms.Description:
You stand before the great cathedral. The doors loom nearly one hundered
meters above your head. Luckily they are already open. A dim light shines
from within the sanctuary. As you stand here you feel at peace with the 
universe.

rooms.Name: In the grand entrance way.
rooms.Description:
This is the grand entranceway to the great cathedral. Above you the arched
ceiling stretches nearly two hundered metres above you. The walls and ceiling
are made of a golden metal. The floors are covered in ornate red and gold 
carpets. The hall is lit by a soft light with no apparent source.

rooms.Name: A long hallway.
rooms.Description:
The hallway continues north and south within the cathedral. The walls are
covered with great stain glass windows. The windows provide the room with
a peacefull light. As you continue down the hall you notice several robed
figures pass silently by. To the north you can see an intersection in the
hallway.

ExtraDescs.Description:
The stain glass windows depict a great battle. Warriors in huge suits of
armor fight great deformed red demons. Above the battlefield flies a great
white dragon with icy blue eyes.

rooms.Name: An intersection.
rooms.Description:
You stand at the intersection of a hallway that runs east and west. Doors
line both sides of these hallways and to the south is the entrance to the
cathedral. At the north end of this intersection is a set of closed doors
carved from dark brown wood.  You hear the muted sound of a pipe organ
playing through the thick doors.

rooms.Name: In the sanctuary.
rooms.Description:
You stand at the south end of a very large sanctuary. The room is
lit by a large stain glass window above the altar. To your left and
right are several rows of pews. The ceiling streches hundereds of
feet over head. The room is filled with the sound of a pipe organ
playing ancient hymns.

rooms.Name: The east wing.
rooms.Description:
The east wing of the cathedral is used for housing purposes. To the north and
south are the clergy chambers. Light fills the room from a skylight overhead.
The hall is completely quiet. Every so often a robed figure passes silently
through the halls.

rooms.Name: The west wing.
rooms.Description:
The main hallway of the west wing is smaller than the rest of the hallways
you have seen so far. The halls are completely silent. Light flows in from
several windows along the walls. There are open doors to the north and south.

rooms.Name: Further down the eastern wing.
rooms.Description:
The hallway widens and comes to an end. To the north and south are more quarters
used by the clergy. To the west the hallway continues. Set deep within the
eastern wall is a huge oaken door. From the other side of the door you can
hear chanting, and humming. Strange smells escape from beneath the door.

rooms.Name: A winding passage.
rooms.Description:
The hallway turns into a small passagway, only about two feet wide.
Back to the west, you can see an intersection off in the distance.
The passage turns sharply, and continues to the north. The walls
begin to lean inward here. Light shines in from the west, and north.

rooms.Name: Before a sturdy metal door.
rooms.Description:
You stand before a sturdy metal door. The metal apears iron, or
perhaps steel. The door has been engraved with intricate designs. 
Next to the door is a small controll panel. The lights on the
panel flicker, and pulse every few seconds.

rooms.Name: An unlit room.
rooms.Description:
You light barely manages to illuminate this dark corner in the cathedral.
As you gaze around you discover yourself in a small dusty room.
There is a table in the center, and shelves lining three of the four walls.
The shelves and table are covered in odds and ends used in a church.

rooms.Name: Standing before the altar.
rooms.Description:
You stand before the altar of the great cathedral. Light shines in
from above through a large stain glass window. The alter is made of
a solid piece of granite. On the alter is a large golden cross, and
two large golden offering plates.

rooms.Name: A small antechamber.
rooms.Description:
You have found a small coat room. The walls are made of stone, and are
lined with coat racks. The only light comes in through the doorway
that leads to the main hallway.

rooms.Name: A small antechamber.
rooms.Description:
You have found a small coat room. The walls are made of stone, and are
lined with coat racks. The only light comes in through the doorway
that leads to the main hallway.

rooms.Name: The private chambers of one of the clergy.
rooms.Description:
The room is bare except for a bed and a small table. The room is
exceptionally clean. There is no dust on the floor, and the bed
is made. The only light comes in from a window high over the bed.

rooms.Name: The private chambers of one of the clergy.
rooms.Description:
The room is bare except for a bed and a small table. The room is
exceptionally clean. There is no dust on the floor, and the bed
is made. The only light comes in from a window high over the bed.

rooms.Name: The private chambers of one of the clergy.
rooms.Description:
The room is bare except for a bed and a small table. The room is
exceptionally clean. There is no dust on the floor, and the bed
is made. The only light comes in from a window high over the bed.

rooms.Name: The private chambers of one of the clergy.
rooms.Description:
The room is bare except for a bed and a small table. The room is
exceptionally clean. There is no dust on the floor, and the bed
is made. The only light comes in from a window high over the bed.

rooms.Name: The pennance chamber.
rooms.Description:
This is the room where the clergy pay pennance for thier sins. The
walls are covered with racks full of instruments of torture. There
are also fasting chambers. The room is dark except for your light,
which combined with all the whips, and scourges give the room a less
than holy aura.

rooms.Name: The private chambers of one of the clergy.
rooms.Description:
The room is bare except for a bed and a small table. The room is
exceptionally clean. There is no dust on the floor, and the bed
is made. The only light comes in from a window high over the bed.

rooms.Name: The private chambers of one of the clergy.
rooms.Description:
The room is bare except for a bed and a small table. The room is
exceptionally clean. There is no dust on the floor, and the bed
is made. The only light comes in from a window high over the bed.

rooms.Name: The entrance to the great library.
rooms.Description:
This is the entrance to the great library of the cathedral. You can
see shelves of books streching several hundered meters in all
directions. Above you the ceiling streches fifty feet above you.

rooms.Name: Among the shelves of books
rooms.Description:
You stand among the many shelves of books in the great library.
The shelves strech in all directions, and all the way to the ceiling.
You are very confused...

rooms.Name: Among the shelves of books
rooms.Description:
You stand among the many shelves of books in the great library.
The shelves strech in all directions, and all the way to the ceiling.
You are very confused...

rooms.Name: Among the shelves of books
rooms.Description:
You stand among the many shelves of books in the great library.
The shelves strech in all directions, and all the way to the ceiling.
You are very confused...

rooms.Description:
You stand among the many shelves of books in the great library.
The shelves strech in all directions, and all the way to the ceiling.
You are very confused...

rooms.Description:
You stand among the many shelves of books in the great library.
The shelves strech in all directions, and all the way to the ceiling.
You are very confused...

rooms.Description:
You stand among the many shelves of books in the great library.
The shelves strech in all directions, and all the way to the ceiling.
You are very confused...

rooms.Name: Among the shelves of books
rooms.Description:
You stand among the many shelves of books in the great library.
The shelves strech in all directions, and all the way to the ceiling.
You are very confused...

rooms.Name: A secluded room.
rooms.Description:
You have found a secluded room in the library. The room is only a few
meters wide. The room is lit by an odd light with no apparent source.
The walls are lined with book covered shelves. In the center of the
room is a large oaken desk covered in papers, and books. A smokey
haze filles the room, and a pungent odor assaults your senses.

rooms.Name: On the parapets of the cathedral.
rooms.Description:
You have managed to climb up through the skylight, and onto the roof
of the great cathedral. All around you are the paraets, and turrets you saw
from the ground. Off in the distance, far above you in the sky, you
can see what looks like some kind of ship. Below you on the ground
you can hear the boom of thrusters as several fighter craft, and troop
transports lift off. You can see more papapets to the east,
and west.

rooms.Name: The eastern missile battery.
rooms.Description:
There are several turrets here, as well as a large missile
battery. It appears capable of holding well over ten thousand short
range missiles. The main launcher is also equiped with quad las
cannons. The cannons have not yet begun to fire, but every few seconds
they move slightly as they track the ship through the sky.

rooms.Name: Next to a small building on the roof.
rooms.Description:
There are several turrets here slowly tracking the ship through the
sky. To the south is a snall building. The walls are made of a thick
grey metal. There is a door on the north side. The door has no
apparent handles or knobs. However, next to the door is an instrument
pannel. Lights on the pannel periodically flicker, and pulse.

rooms.Name: A forgotten room.
rooms.Description:
You stand in a building on top of the cathedral. The floors and ceiling
are made of stone. The walls are covered by shelves piled with books.
In the middle of the room is a long table. The table is made of oak,
and is covered in books and parchments. On the table is a very large
candle that sheds light on the room.

rooms.Name: A grey metal corridor.
rooms.Description:
The scenery dramatically changes at this point. You find yourself 
in a grey metal corridor. The low ceiling is covered with pipes, and
flourescent lamps. You can hear the humof engines to the south, and
several footsteps to the east and west.

rooms.Name: Before huge metal doors.
rooms.Description:
You stand before a set of large metal double doors. On the floor before
the doors are yellow and black lines. A red light above the door flashes
every few seconds. From behind the door you can hear men shouting, and the hum
rumble of engines. To the south the hall way comes to a T intersection.

rooms.Name: Outside the quartermaster's office.
rooms.Description:
You stand in a small grey metal corridor. To the north and south are
doors leading to the barracks. To the east however is a door leading to
the quartermaster's office. The door looksexactly like all the others
except there are no handles or knobs. Instead there is a glowing
keypad next to the door. From the other side of the door you can hear
voices, and footsteps. To the north and south you hear several more
voices and footsteps.

rooms.Name: A thin corridor.
rooms.Description:
The corridor is only a few feet wide at this point. The walls and floor
are made of a greyish metal. The corridor runs from east to west. The north
and south walls are lined with doors. You can hear the faint hum of
machinery to the east. The air grows think and pungent the more
west ward you travel.

rooms.Name: Inside a barracks.
rooms.Description:
You have found one of the barracks used by the space marine troops
stationed here. The walls are lined with shelf like beds. Beneath each
bed is a locker. Several of the beds are in use, but the majority of
them are currently vaccant.

rooms.Name: Inside a barracks.
rooms.Description:
You have found one of the barracks used by the space marine troops
stationed here. The walls are lined with shelf like beds. Beneath each
bed is a locker. Several of the beds are in use, but the majority of
them are currently vaccant.

rooms.Name: The end of the corridor.
rooms.Description:
You have come to the end of the corridor. To the north and south are
more doors leading to the barracks. To the west is a large steel door.
Steam comes out from underneath the door. The air near the door is
thick, hot, and smells of rotting flesh.

rooms.Name: Inside a barracks.
rooms.Description:
You have found one of the barracks used by the space marine troops
stationed here. The walls are lined with shelf like beds. Beneath each
bed is a locker. Several of the beds are in use, but the majority of
them are currently vaccant.

rooms.Name: Inside a barracks.
rooms.Description:
You have found one of the barracks used by the space marine troops
stationed here. The walls are lined with shelf like beds. Beneath each
bed is a locker. Several of the beds are in use, but the majority of
them are currently vaccant.

rooms.Name: In the mess.
rooms.Description:
The room stinks of rotting flesh. The room is lined with tables, filled
with men hurredly eating goop on trays. To the north you can see men
standing in a line to get this stuff. Whatever it is they apparently
like it. There are also several men in aprons scurrying to and fro
cleaning up the mess left by the soldiers.

rooms.Name: The kitchen.
rooms.Description:
You have found the source of the horrible assault to your senses.
You stand amidst steam, and sweaty men in threadbare t-shirts. In the
center of the room is a huge metal cauldron. Several men using long
wooden poles stir the dubious contents. While others use shovels to
heap the sludge into the serving bins. A cook stands in the back of the
room smoking a cigar, and shouting orders to the rest of the men.

rooms.Name: Inside a barracks.
rooms.Description:
You have found one of the barracks used by the space marine troops
stationed here. The walls are lined with shelf like beds. Beneath each
bed is a locker. Several of the beds are in use, but the majority of
them are currently vaccant.

rooms.Name: Inside a barracks.
rooms.Description:
You have found one of the barracks used by the space marine troops
stationed here. The walls are lined with shelf like beds. Beneath each
bed is a locker. Several of the beds are in use, but the majority of
them are currently vaccant.

rooms.Name: The quartermaster's office.
rooms.Description:
You have entered a plush office. As you look around, the only hint that
you are in a military instalation is given by the grey pipes lining the
ceiling. The walls are made of wood, the floor is carpeted. In the
center of the room is a large oaken desk. The desk is piled high with
papers. Also on the desk is a paper wieght shapped like an old Civil
War cannon.

rooms.Name: The docking bay.
rooms.Description:
All around you troops file aboard troop transports, as fighter crafts
are launched ahead. Several officers bark orders to the troops. You
can see a wide variety of armaments being loaded onto a nearby craft.
Everything from las cannons, to chainswords are unpacked from crates and
handed to troops as they board.

rooms.Name: Aboard the troop transport.
rooms.Description:
As you enter the craft troops begin strapping themselves into the seats
lining the walls of the craft.  After several seconds the entrance ramp is
raised and the loading doors close.  The engines begin to hum louder and louder.
Within seconds you can no longer hear anything else.  Then suddenly
you are thrown to the ground as the craft leaps into the air.  You
manage to stabalize yourself by grabbing hold onto a nearby marine.  The craft is
several times, and begins to shake violently.  You hear a voice 
from the cabin announc "We have touched down.  Exit, and procede north
to the rondevou.  Warning all troops! We are now in direct confrontation
with enemy troops!"  You have a bad feeling about this...
Maybe now would be a good time to turn back...

rooms.Name: Aboard the alien craft.
rooms.Description:
The transport had managed to touch down inside the enemy craft. Apparenlty
it was equipped with a device that allowed it to cling to the hull while
troops were injected into the craft. All around you are marines running, and
ducking for cover. Ahead to the north you can see flashes of light
and hear heavy gunfire.

rooms.Name: Aboard the troop transport.
rooms.Description:
There dosn't seem to be near as many troops making the return voyage
as there were going into battle.  Either these guys love to fight or
they died real fast.  You hear a gentle clang as the ship slides into
the docking bay.  If only the ride up had been as smooth.  A voice from
the cabin announces "You may depart and report to your assigned positions now."
The ship doors slide open and you ca see the docking bay below you.

rooms.Name: Standing at the end of a smoke filled corridor.
rooms.Description:
You stand at one end of a smoke filled corridor. To the north all you can see
is smoke. You can hear the rapid pulsing of a las cannon, and several bursts
of gunfire from automatic weapons. Periodicaly you hear explosions, and the
whole room shakes. To the south you can hear troops shouting, and more gunfire
as marines infiltrate the ship. Above you is a small metal hatch in the ceiling.
There are black and yellow caution stripes around the hatch.

rooms.Name: In a smoke filled passage.
rooms.Description:
All you can see is smoke. The echos of gunfire all around you make it
nearly impossible to find your way.

rooms.Name: A gunnery pod.
rooms.Description:
You stand in a cramped gunnery pod. There is just enough room for one person
to sit in the gunners seat. Above you is a glass bubble dome. Outside you can
see a swarm of fighter craft engaged in dogfights, and making bombing runs on
the alien ship. You can also see several troop transports slowly making their
way towards you.

rooms.Name: In a smoke filled passage.
rooms.Description:
All you can see is smoke. The echos of gunfire all around you make it
nearly impossible to find your way.

rooms.Name: In a smoke filled passage.
rooms.Description:
All you can see is smoke. The echos of gunfire all around you make it
nearly impossible to find your way.

rooms.Name: In a smoke filled passage.
rooms.Description:
All you can see is smoke. The echos of gunfire all around you make it
nearly impossible to find your way.

rooms.Name: In a smoke filled passage.
rooms.Description:
All you can see is smoke. The echos of gunfire all around you make it
nearly impossible to find your way.

rooms.Name: In a smoke filled passage.
rooms.Description:
The room is too filled with smoke to see anything. Anything that is except
a small red light near the floor.

OUCH! That REALLY HURT!

As you come to your senses the memory of recent events slowly returns. The
flash of light, the deafening boom, the soul rending pain, and all the blood...
The smoke has intensified, but as you return to your feet you realize the the
room is several degrees hotter.

rooms.Name: In a smoke filled passage.
rooms.Description:
The room is completely filled with smoke. You can barely make out the...

OUCH! That REALLY hurt!

As the world comes into focus, you make a promise to yourself _never_ to
underestimate anti-tank fire again. The explosion created even more smoke,
and combined with your headache, it is now quite impossible find your way.

rooms.Name: Before a smoke filled passage.
rooms.Description:
You stand in a controll room of some kind. To the east is a smoke filled
passage. You can hear the sounds of gunfire to the east. To the north is
a large metal door that has been blown off its hinges. To the south is
a shimmering red force field blocking a passageway. To the west is a blast
door. Next to the door is a small control pannel with flashing lights.

rooms.Name: A narrow passage.
rooms.Description:
You are in a tight corridor that runs north and south. To the east is a metal
door. To the south is a small control room. To the north the corridor opens
into a larger room.

rooms.Name: Inside a transport tube.
rooms.Description:
You are inside a transport tube. As soon as you step in you notice a control
pannel on the wall. After several seconds the lights on the panel begin to
flash, and the tube begins to move.

rooms.Name: A narrow passage.
rooms.Description:
You stand in a narrow passage that runs east and west. The floor and walls are
constructed of a greyish metal material. Overhead is a network of pipes and
vents. Steam leaks from several of the pipes, and clouds the passage.

rooms.Name: A control room overlooking the shuttle bay.
rooms.Description:
You stand in a small five by five room. To the west is a small corridor. The
north, and south walls of the room are covered with monitors, and instruments
of all kinds. To the east is a large glass window overlooking the docking bay.
The bay is bustling with troops. Crews hurredly prepare fighter craft for
the assault.

rooms.Name: In the docking bay.
rooms.Description:
You have found the docking bay of the spacecraft. The bay is nearly five
hundered feet in length, and a hundered feet high. The floor is made of
thick concrete, the walls are made of a greyish metal, a network of pipes
run overhead. The room is filled from wall to wall with small fighter craft.
The hang on racks, and are slowly being launched from the ship.

rooms.Name: A missile bay.
rooms.Description:
You stand in a huge room. It is nearly a hundered feet in lenght. The room
is filled with missiles, and equipment to launch, load, and arm them. There
is a console at on end of the room. It is covered by displays, and lights.
Every few seconds a terminal beeps, and several lights flash.

rooms.Name: Above the reactor core.
rooms.Description:
You are crossing a thin bridge hundreds of feet above the reactor core. Below
you, you can see a bright light, and feel an intense heat. Every few minutes a
wave of energy pulses up the shaft.

rooms.Name: Falling into the reactor!
rooms.Description:
You have taken a wrong step, and are now paying the price. As you fall to
certain doom, you think to yourself how nice it will be to get away from it
all.

rooms.Name: In a transport tube.
rooms.Description:
You are inside a small transport tube. On the wall is a small instrument
pannel. After a few seconds the tube begins to move.

rooms.Name: On the main control deck.
rooms.Description:
You stand on the main control deck of the ship. All around you are lights
and screens. Every few seconds alarms go off, and lights flicker. On several
screens you can see the cathedral, and fighters engaging the ground targets.

rooms.Name: The upper control room.
rooms.Description:
This is a small room just big enough for one person. In the center is a desk.
The walls around the desk are covered  with monitors. The desk is covered with
lights and control pannels. Every few seconds lights flash, and beeps sound.
